Then, let us compute number of new shares which is computed by dividing the rights offering by the net proceeds per share.  As an illustration, here's what it looks like: 


$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Number of new shares }&=\dfrac{\text{\$4.7 million}}{\text{\$28.20}}\\[10pt]
&={\textbf{166,667 shares}}
\end{aligned}$$ 

**The total number of new shares is 166,667 shares.**
